# Local Hermes Agent patch: remember session-only /model switches across restarts.
#
# Purpose
# - Keep the user's configured model.default/model.provider as the static fallback.
# - Persist every successful /model switch to model.last_used_model and
#   model.last_used_provider, including session-only switches.
# - Make new `hermes` and `hermes --tui` instances prefer last_used_* when
#   present, then fall back to model.default/model.provider.
#
# Important invariants for future rebases
# - Do NOT make session-only /model switches overwrite model.default or
#   model.provider; those are only updated for explicit global persistence.
# - Preserve atomic config writes via the existing save_config_value()/save_config
#   helpers; do not add ad-hoc YAML writers.
# - Keep provider and model together: model strings are ambiguous across
#   providers, so last_used_provider must be persisted/read with last_used_model.
# - TUI _persist_model_switch(..., persist_global=False) should write only
#   last_used_*; persist_global=True may additionally update default/provider
#   and base_url.
#
# Main code touch points in upstream source
# - cli.py: HermesCLI startup resolution and both /model switch paths.
# - tui_gateway/server.py: startup runtime resolution and TUI /model persistence.
# - hermes_cli/oneshot.py, gateway/run.py, agent/auxiliary_client.py: startup /
#   helper resolution paths that should prefer last_used_model.
# - hermes_cli/auth.py: legacy/global model-choice helper should set
#   last_used_model too when it changes model.default.
# - tests/hermes_cli/test_last_used_model.py: regression coverage.
#
# Rebase workflow
# 1. Apply this patch to a clean hermes-agent checkout with `git apply --check`
#    then `git apply`.
# 2. If hunks fail, search upstream for the functions named above and re-apply
#    the invariants rather than matching line numbers.
# 3. Regenerate from the hermes-agent checkout with:
#      git diff --binary -- \
#        agent/auxiliary_client.py cli.py gateway/run.py hermes_cli/auth.py \
#        hermes_cli/oneshot.py tui_gateway/server.py \
#        tests/hermes_cli/test_last_used_model.py \
#        > ~/.config/nixpkgs/usr/cli/ai/hermes/remember-last-used-model.patch
# 4. Keep this comment header at the top after regeneration.
#
# Verification used when this patch was added
# - Targeted tests under a Nix Python env: tests/hermes_cli/test_last_used_model.py
#   and tests/cli/test_cli_save_config_value.py.
# - Nix build of this module's hermes-agent derivation.
#
